The Predator | Official Trailer [HD] | 20th Century FOX
Comment:
Haven't seen this yet, but I look forward to seeing it despite the mixed reviews to make up my own mind. Saw a few clips posted on YouTube, which impressed me, as you have finally... *FINALLY* included the Yautja dialogue. Quite frankly, if there's to be another Predator film, I would rather see the Predators themselves as central characters and jump more into their culture with much more dialogue between them, studying the humans etc.

The Predator franchise has come such a long way since the first film. The Predator isn't just a background villain anymore. In the wake of dozens and dozens of comic books, novels, games, maybe it's time to do a film, or even a short TV series of a few episodes, that focuses mostly and solely on the Predators themselves: hunts, traditions, honour, dishonour, clans, bloodlines... I'm sure a majority of Predator fans would be interested in possibly seeing this as opposed to the usual formula, which has been present in 3 of the 4 movies, as I've not seen this 4th instalment yet.

Title: The Predator | Official Trailer [HD] | 20th Century FOX
Comment:
Alright, just saw the movie tonight.
AVOID AT ALL COSTS
It's terrible. Awful. Worse than Predators, and that's hard to do.
The CGI looks worse than it did in AVP, which is shocking. 
They made fun of mental disorders throughout the ENTIRE movie. A few jokes of that sort are fine, and don't bother me, but they did it the ENTIRE film. 
They tried too hard to be like the original, as well. Butchered lines from the original, tried to re-crate the "rag tag" band of soldiers, but horribly failed.
I'd say the worst offender in this movie, by far, is how awful the effects were. I seriously don't think they were finished with them, but had to release the film. The blood has a weird 3D CGI look to it, both the human, and predator blood. The ships looked pretty bad, and the predators themselves looked pretty bad with their masks off.

Do NOT waste your time or money with this film. If you REALLY want to see it, wait until it comes out on streaming.

Comment:
If I was going to make a new Predator movie, I would say ok here are the ground rules:
1) You can't make it about some other creature or alter the predators to be larger or more lethal - that is cheap and not how you make a movie "better".
2) It must be Rated "R".
3) No puns or one-liners.
4) We must learn something new and interesting about the Predators, but you can't reveal everything, it can't contradict what we know, and it can't be the basis of the whole plot.
5) The hero must be intelligent and not make stupid decisions.
6) It can't be "personal" - the hero is doing what they are because they are a HERO - not because they want revenge, or are trapped and have no choice, or they didn't give a crap until it was their loved one in danger. A good person to sympathize with and care about.
7) It must be suspenseful, intelligent, intense, and creative.
8) No standard predictable 'Hollywood ending'.
9) It must be scientifically feasible within the sci-fi parameters already established.
10) It must have a diversity of pacing - some slow parts, character development, interspersed with action parts. It can't just be nonstop loud noises and action from start to finish where you couldn't care less about what happens.

What if... a Predator was a recurring character? Not a different predator that always loses, but a Predator that always wins..
